CNCP v1 23133
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12405: `:global` doesn't work with CSS nesting",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:45.431106+00:00",
  "text": "`:global` doesn't work with CSS nesting\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n@d637bd6\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nIn the minimal reproduction, open the Playground's compiled CSS tab.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\n```css\r\nbody {\r\n  background-color: blue;\r\nh1[data-v-7ba5bd90] {\r\n    background-color: purple;\r\n}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n```css\r\nbody {\r\n&[data-v-7ba5bd90] {\r\n  background-color: blue;\r\n}\r\nh1[data-v-7ba5bd90] {\r\n    background-color: purple;\r\n}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\nRemove the nested `h1` selector inside `:global(body)`, and then the body's background becomes blue as expected.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: sfc",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
